const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How much does floor sanding cost in Monaghan?",
    answer: "Floor sanding prices in County Monaghan typically range from €25-€40 per square metre, depending on floor condition and finish type. We offer free, no-obligation quotes for all Monaghan properties. Call 087 402 7101 for a competitive local rate."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does floor sanding take in a typical Monaghan home?",
    answer: "Most residential floor sanding projects in Monaghan take 2-3 days. A single room can often be completed in one day, while a full house may take 3-5 days. We'll give you an accurate timeline during your free consultation."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you cover all of County Monaghan?",
    answer: "Yes, we cover every town and townland in County Monaghan. Based in Scotstown, we're centrally located to reach Carrickmacross, Castleblayney, Clones, Ballybay, Monaghan Town, Emyvale, and Glaslough quickly. We also cover border areas into Armagh and Fermanagh."
  },
  {
    question: "Is floor sanding messy?",
    answer: "We use modern dust-free sanding equipment that captures 99% of dust. Your Monaghan home stays clean throughout the process. We also protect all furniture, fixtures, and adjoining rooms."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you sand parquet floors in older Monaghan houses?",
    answer: "Absolutely. Many period homes in Monaghan feature original parquet or herringbone floors. We specialise in restoring these beautiful heritage floors while preserving their character. We've restored floors in Georgian townhouses, Victorian villas, and traditional farmhouses across the county."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you offer commercial floor sanding in Monaghan?",
    answer: "Yes, we work with pubs, restaurants, hotels, offices, and shops throughout County Monaghan. We can schedule work outside business hours to minimise disruption. We've completed projects in Carrickmacross and Castleblayney town centres."
  }
];
